==神经突的发育==

神经突的发育需要细胞内外的信号之间进行复杂的相互作用。在发育过程中，遍布于整个神经突的特殊受体会检测周围的空间是否适合生长。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last1=Valtorta|first1=F.|last2=Leoni|first2=C.|date=1999-02-28|title=Molecular mechanisms of neurite extension|journal=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. Series B, Biological Sciences|volume=354|issue=1381|pages=387–394|doi=10.1098/rstb.1999.0391|issn=0962-8436|pmc=1692490|pmid=10212488}}</ref> 神经突会通过处理所有来自受体的信息来决定该朝哪个方向生长。<ref name=":0" />发展中的神经元会将所有的生长信号汇总在一起，并以此来决定神经元最终将会向哪个方向生长。<ref name=":0" /> 在已知的细胞外生长信号中，{{le|netrin|netrin|netrin}}，一种中线化学引诱剂，以及{{le|semaphorin|semaphorin|semaphorin}}、{{le|ephrin|ephrin|ephrin}}和{{le|Collapsin response mediator protein family|collapsin|Collapsin response mediator protein family|collapsin|Collapsin response mediator protein family|collapsin}}，都是神经突生长的抑制剂。<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Niclou|first1=Simone P.|last2=Franssen|first2=Elske H. P.|last3=Ehlert|first3=Erich M. E.|last4=Taniguchi|first4=Masahiko|last5=Verhaagen|first5=Joost|date=2003-12-01|title=Meningeal cell-derived semaphorin 3A inhibits neurite outgrowth|journal=Molecular and Cellular Neurosciences|volume=24|issue=4|pages=902–912|issn=1044-7431|pmid=14697657|doi=10.1016/s1044-7431(03)00243-4|s2cid=12637023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Luo|first1=Y.|last2=Raible|first2=D.|last3=Raper|first3=J. A.|date=1993-10-22|title=Collapsin: a protein in brain that induces the collapse and paralysis of neuronal growth cones|journal=Cell|volume=75|issue=2|pages=217–227|issn=0092-8674|pmid=8402908|doi=10.1016/0092-8674(93)80064-l|s2cid=46120825}}</ref>

早期的神经突通常充满了[[微管|微管]]束，其生长受到{{le|神经营养因子|neurotrophic factors|神经营养因子}}的刺激，如{{le|神经生长因子|nerve growth factor|神经生长因子}}（NGF）。<ref>Bear, Mark F; Connors, Barry W.; Paradiso, Michael A., [https://books.google.com/books?id=75NgwLzueikC&printsec=frontcover&dq=neuroscience+exploring+the+brain ''Neuroscience, Exploring the Brain''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=75NgwLzueikC&printsec=frontcover&dq=neuroscience+exploring+the+brain |date=20211203143542 }}, Philadelphia : Lippincott Williams & Wilkins; Third Edition (February 1, 2006). {{ISBN|0-7817-6003-8}}</ref> [[Tau蛋白|Tau蛋白]]可以通过与微管结合来帮助稳定微管，保护其不受微管切断蛋白的影响。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Qiang |first1=Liang |last2=Yu |first2=Wenqian |last3=Andreadis |first3=Athena |last4=Luo |first4=Minhua |last5=Baas |first5=Peter W. |title=Tau Protects Microtubules in the Axon from Severing by Katanin |journal=The Journal of Neuroscience |date=22 March 2006 |volume=26 |issue=12 |pages=3120–3129 |doi=10.1523/JNEUROSCI.5392-05.2006 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6674103/ |issn=0270-6474}}</ref>神经元的[[细胞骨架|细胞骨架]]在微管稳定后仍保持动态。肌动蛋白丝在将成为轴突的神经突中仍保持其动态的特性，以此来推动微管束向外延伸轴突。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Xiao|first1=Yangui|last2=Peng|first2=Yinghui|last3=Wan|first3=Jun|last4=Tang|first4=Genyun|last5=Chen|first5=Yuewen|last6=Tang|first6=Jing|last7=Ye|first7=Wen-Cai|last8=Ip|first8=Nancy Y.|last9=Shi|first9=Lei|date=2013-07-05|title=The Atypical Guanine Nucleotide Exchange Factor Dock4 Regulates Neurite Differentiation through Modulation of Rac1 GTPase and Actin Dynamics|journal=Journal of Biological Chemistry|language=en|volume=288|issue=27|pages=20034–20045|doi=10.1074/jbc.M113.458612|issn=0021-9258|pmc=3707701|pmid=23720743}}</ref> 然而，在所有其他的神经突中，肌动蛋白丝会被肌球蛋白稳定下来。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Toriyama|first1=Michinori|last2=Kozawa|first2=Satoshi|last3=Sakumura|first3=Yuichi|last4=Inagaki|first4=Naoyuki|date=2013-03-18|title=Conversion of a signal into forces for axon outgrowth through Pak1-mediated shootin1 phosphorylation|journal=Current Biology|volume=23|issue=6|pages=529–534|doi=10.1016/j.cub.2013.02.017|issn=1879-0445|pmid=23453953|doi-access=free}}</ref> 这防止了多轴突的发育。
